summary.$t:
High speed photography by Alan Sailer, California, America - Sep 2011...Manadatory Credit: Photo by Alan Sailer / Rex Features (1444198ab)
 Cigarettes shot with an air rifle pellet
 High speed photography by Alan Sailer, California, America - Sep 2011
 FULL WORDS LINK: http://www.rexfeatures.com/nanolink/dqiy  What an impressive shot!  Alan Sailer creates amazing images of everyday items being hit by projectiles.  Using high-speed photography, he can capture in stunning detail the moment items such as marbles and pellets pass through objects.  The jaw-dropping results include a pellet shredding three cigarettes, a marble destroying an ice cream cone and the shooting of stacks of staples.  Other targeted highlights include cans of drink, ice lollies, a cherry pie and a tub of cream cheese.  Based in Camarillo, California, the 56-year-old is a microwave engineer by day, but pursues his hobby in his garage in the evening.  His set-up allows him the option to not only fire pellets and marbles at 500ft per second, but items such as Christmas ornaments filled with coloured gelatine.
